    {
      "id": "9d63fe8dd80f8674da89895d9d7940a7e2be643f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-03-09 15:57:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nThe only possible issue is '-' not being listed first inside [], but if the current patch works in happy with it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b2193ece9b0f8c9fa4fd7ae13868a1d167555cec",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 296,
        "name": "Frank Heckes",
        "email": "Frank.Heckes@intel.com",
        "username": "Frank.Heckes",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-03-10 16:26:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOrder doesn't seems to matter:\n('-' first in sed)\n[fheckes@shadow-1]$ echo \"2.6.32-431.29.2.el6.ppc64\" | sed -e 's/\\.x86_64$//' -e 's/\\.i[3456]86$//' -e 's/-smp$//' -e 's/-bigsmp$//' -e 's/[-\\.]ppc64$//' -e 's/-default$//'\n2.6.32-431.29.2.el6\n[fheckes@shadow-1 $ echo \"2.6.32-431.29.2.el6-ppc64\" | sed -e 's/\\.x86_64$//' -e 's/\\.i[3456]86$//' -e 's/-smp$//' -e 's/-bigsmp$//' -e 's/[-\\.]ppc64$//' -e 's/-default$//'\n2.6.32-431.29.2.el6\n\n('-' last in sed):\n[fheckes@shadow-1 ]$ echo \"2.6.32-431.29.2.el6.ppc64\" | sed -e 's/\\.x86_64$//' -e 's/\\.i[3456]86$//' -e 's/-smp$//' -e 's/-bigsmp$//' -e 's/[\\.-]ppc64$//' -e 's/-default$//'\n2.6.32-431.29.2.el6\n[fheckes@shadow-1 ]$ echo \"2.6.32-431.29.2.el6-ppc64\" | sed -e 's/\\.x86_64$//' -e 's/\\.i[3456]86$//' -e 's/-smp$//' -e 's/-bigsmp$//' -e 's/[\\.-]ppc64$//' -e 's/-default$//'\n2.6.32-431.29.2.el6\nAnyway I think I push a new patch to be on save side.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "016b9e83778a0f95cf47c7fdcd18f6ebabaa7aee",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-03-10 17:37:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe sed man page says that having '-' first or last in the list is correct. Note that '.' Does not need to be escaped inside [], so the current regexp is also matching '\\'.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
